<HL>
   Business Brief -- Turner Corp.:
   Switzerland's Karl Steiner
   And Unit Form New Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
09/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TUR
</CO>
<IN>
HOME CONSTRUCTION (HOM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Turner Corp. said its subsidiary, Turner International
Industries Inc., formed a new company with Karl Steiner Ltd.
of Switzerland to pursue construction-related opportunities
in Europe.
   Based in Brussels, Turner Steiner Europe Inc. will offer
consulting and management services to clients with building
plans in Europe.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Based in New York, Turner, a holding company that operates
several construction subsidiaries, is one of the largest
general builders in the country. Karl Steiner is a general
contracting, design and construction company with
subsidiaries in France, Germany and Italy.
</TEXT>
